---
/** Scoring formats overview page. Ported from react/pages/Scoring.tsx. */
import Base from "../../layouts/Base.astro";
import BackLink from "../../components/BackLink.astro";
---

<Base title="GlideComp - Scoring">
  <div class="min-h-screen bg-background text-foreground p-6">
    <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto">
      <header class="mb-10">
        <BackLink href="/" />
        <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold flex items-center gap-3">
          <img src="/icon.svg" alt="GlideComp logo" class="w-8 h-8" />
          Scoring
        </h1>
        <p class="text-muted-foreground mt-1">How GlideComp scores competitions</p>
      </header>

      <section class="mb-10">
        <div class="space-y-4 text-sm leading-relaxed">
          <p class="text-muted-foreground">
            Every GlideComp competition is scored with one of two formats, chosen by the
            organiser in the competition settings. Pick a format below to read how it works in
            detail.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      {/* GAP */}
      <a
        href="/scoring/gap"
        class="block mb-6 p-5 rounded-lg border border-border bg-card hover:border-primary/60 transition-colors group"
      >
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between mb-2">
          <h2 class="text-xl font-bold">
            GAP <span class="text-sm font-normal text-muted-foreground">race to goal</span>
          </h2>
          <svg
            xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
            width="18"
            height="18"
            viewBox="0 0 24 24"
            fill="none"
            stroke="currentColor"
            stroke-width="2"
            stroke-linecap="round"
            stroke-linejoin="round"
            class="text-muted-foreground group-hover:text-foreground transition-colors"
          >
            <line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12" />
            <polyline points="12 5 19 12 12 19" />
          </svg>
        </div>
        <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
          The standard CIVL scoring used at most paragliding and hang gliding competitions.
          Pilots race a set course through turnpoints to a goal. A perfect task day is worth 1000
          points, shared between distance, time, leading and arrival based on how each pilot
          performed relative to the field. Best for tasks with a defined route and goal.
        </p>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-sm font-medium mt-3 text-foreground group-hover:underline">
          Read how GAP works
          <svg
            xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
            width="14"
            height="14"
            viewBox="0 0 24 24"
            fill="none"
            stroke="currentColor"
            stroke-width="2"
            stroke-linecap="round"
            stroke-linejoin="round"
          >
            <line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12" />
            <polyline points="12 5 19 12 12 19" />
          </svg>
        </span>
      </a>

      {/* Open Distance */}
      <a
        href="/scoring/open-distance"
        class="block mb-6 p-5 rounded-lg border border-border bg-card hover:border-primary/60 transition-colors group"
      >
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between mb-2">
          <h2 class="text-xl font-bold">
            Open distance
            <span class="text-sm font-normal text-muted-foreground">
              fly as far as you can
            </span>
          </h2>
          <svg
            xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
            width="18"
            height="18"
            viewBox="0 0 24 24"
            fill="none"
            stroke="currentColor"
            stroke-width="2"
            stroke-linecap="round"
            stroke-linejoin="round"
            class="text-muted-foreground group-hover:text-foreground transition-colors"
          >
            <line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12" />
            <polyline points="12 5 19 12 12 19" />
          </svg>
        </div>
        <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
          Everyone launches from the same spot and flies as far as they can, with no set goal.
          Each task has a single take-off turnpoint, and your score is simply the metres of open
          distance flown — the straight-line distance from the point you leave the take-off
          cylinder to the furthest point you reached. Best for free-distance and record-style
          days.
        </p>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-sm font-medium mt-3 text-foreground group-hover:underline">
          Read how open distance works
          <svg
            xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
            width="14"
            height="14"
            viewBox="0 0 24 24"
            fill="none"
            stroke="currentColor"
            stroke-width="2"
            stroke-linecap="round"
            stroke-linejoin="round"
          >
            <line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12" />
            <polyline points="12 5 19 12 12 19" />
          </svg>
        </span>
      </a>

      {/* Data cleaning */}
      <a
        href="/scoring/data-cleaning"
        class="block mb-6 p-5 rounded-lg border border-border bg-card hover:border-primary/60 transition-colors group"
      >
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between mb-2">
          <h2 class="text-xl font-bold">
            Track data cleaning
            <span class="text-sm font-normal text-muted-foreground">
              honest inputs to honest scores
            </span>
          </h2>
          <svg
            xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
            width="18"
            height="18"
            viewBox="0 0 24 24"
            fill="none"
            stroke="currentColor"
            stroke-width="2"
            stroke-linecap="round"
            stroke-linejoin="round"
            class="text-muted-foreground group-hover:text-foreground transition-colors"
          >
            <line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12" />
            <polyline points="12 5 19 12 12 19" />
          </svg>
        </div>
        <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
          Flight recorders occasionally log altitudes no glider could fly — GPS dropouts and
          multipath spikes. Before analysis, GlideComp repairs these by cross-checking the GPS
          altitude against the barometric channel, with physical plausibility limits as the
          fallback. Every repair is disclosed on the pilot's score page; positions, times and
          the original file are never altered.
        </p>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-sm font-medium mt-3 text-foreground group-hover:underline">
          Read how data cleaning works
          <svg
            xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
            width="14"
            height="14"
            viewBox="0 0 24 24"
            fill="none"
            stroke="currentColor"
            stroke-width="2"
            stroke-linecap="round"
            stroke-linejoin="round"
          >
            <line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12" />
            <polyline points="12 5 19 12 12 19" />
          </svg>
        </span>
      </a>

    </div>
  </div>
</Base>
